Run this in Powershell to delete all data in ElasticSearch, handy if you just want to rebuild
the index's from scratch

$ Invoke-WebRequest -method DELETE http://localhost:9200/_all

Start ElasticSearch (windows, must be on PATH)

$ elasticsearch.exe

Run python server:

1 - Activate virtual environment if necessary. If venv folder in project root

(git-bash)
$ . venv/Scrips/activate

(windows cmd)
$ "venv/Scripts/activate.bat"

To deactivate simply
$ deactivate

Use parcel to watch for file changes and recompile

$parcel watch index.html